The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Nagaon, Oct. 27: A blast on tracks near Lower Haflong in Assams Dima Hasao derailed a passenger train this noon. The explosion occurred about 25km from the spot where governor J.B. Patnaik inaugurated a festival.          other blast was reported from Mahadevtila forest gate under Haflong police station at 8pm. No one was injured in either incident. District police chief V.K. Ramisetti said an IED, attached to a timer device, triggered the noon explosion.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Union health ministry has decided to allow doctors with a Diplomate of the National Board of Medical Examinations degree to teach, addressing the shortage of faculty in medical colleges. The move is expected to help the nation get 3,000 new medical teachers.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The income tax department has asked Kashmiri separatist leader Syed Ali Shah Geelani to pay Rs 1.73 crore in tax dues after rejecting an eight-year-old appeal by him following the seizure of valuable items from his house in an IT raid.                  
	 Islamabad (PTI): Two teenaged boys accused of hacking the Pakistan Supreme Courts website have admitted that they had committed the crime in collusion with a cyber criminal based in India, the Dawnreported.
                                                                                                                                              
